{"questionId":"9084648","questionHtml":"<p>A body of height 40 cm and uniform cross-sectional area floats in water. 10 cm of the height of the body remains above the water line.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/a0ef850fe59dd28a326d04fbf9e4c82450fefaf3.png\" width=\"376\" height=\"193\"></p>\n<p>The density of water is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ρ</mi></math>. What is the density of the body?</p>\n<p><br>A.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mi>ρ</mi></math></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mi>ρ</mi></math></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mi>ρ</mi></math></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mi>ρ</mi></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>D</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9084648","referenceCode":"EXE.1A.SL.TZ0.2","subjectId":"59-dp-physics-first-assessment-2025","title":"A body of height 40 cm and uniform cross-sectional area floats in water. 10 cm of the height of the body remains above the water line. The density of water is ρ. What is the densit","paper":"1A","level":"SL","questionNumber":"2","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["A. Space, time and motion","A. Space, time and motion","A.2 Forces and momentum"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}